    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Smaller cities on the outskirts of larger metropolitan areas that are independent of the larger city's jurisdiction but dependent on its economic and social orbit. Satellite cities may be planned as such or they may result from ad hoc growth. For planned communities designed to be socially or economically independent of larger metropolitan areas use "new town."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000025571/Abrams, Language of Cities (1971)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010761/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para designar una ciudad más pequeña en las afueras de un área metropolitana mayor, que son independientes de la jurisdicción de las ciudades más grandes, pero que se encuentran dentro de su órbita económica y social.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor kleinere stadskernen aan de rand van grootstedelijke gebieden met een zelfstandige jurisdictie ten opzichte van de grotere stad, maar wel met een zekere mate van economische en sociale afhankelijkheid van die stad. Gebruik 'nieuwe steden' voor gemeenschappen die zijn ontworpen om in sociaal of economisch opzicht onafhankelijk van grotere stedelijke gebieden te fungeren.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleinere Stadt am Rand eines größeren Metropolengebietes, die unabhängig von dessen Gerichtsbarkeit ist, aber von dessen ökonomischen und sozialen Einfluss abhängt. Eine Satellitenstadt kann als solche geplant oder ad hoc gewachsen sein. Für eine geplante Stadt, die gesellschaftlich oder wirtschaftlich unabhängig ist von größeren Metropolengebieten, siehe "Planstadt".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cidades menores na periferia de grandes áreas metropolitanas que são independentes da jurisdição da cidade maior, mas dependem de sua órbita econômica e social. As cidades satélites podem ser planejadas como tal ou podem resultar de um crescimento ad hoc. Para comunidades planejadas projetadas para serem social ou economicamente independentes das grandes áreas metropolitanas, use "cidade nova".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>位於大都會區外緣的小城市，此城市不隸屬於該都市的管轄範圍，但經濟、社會方面則十分依賴該都市。若係指社會或經濟方面獨立於大都會區的規畫社區，則使用「新市鎮」這個名詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
